<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
The product of two expressions <m>(x + {3})</m> and <m>(x + {6})</m> is <m>{24}</m>.
Form a quadratic equation in <m>x</m> and write it in standard quadratic form.
</p>

<p>
<fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
The statement “the product is <m>{24}</m>” means:
</p>

<p>
<me>
(x + {3})(x + {6}) = {24}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Expand the product.
</p>

<p>
<me>
(x + {3})(x + {6}) = x^2 + ({9})x + {18}
</me>
</p>

<p>
So the equation becomes:
</p>

<p>
<me>
x^2 + ({9})x + {18} = {24}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Rearrange to standard form by subtracting <m>{24}</m> from both sides.
</p>

<p>
<me>
x^2 + ({9})x + {18} - {24} = 0
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the required quadratic equation is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\boxed{x^2 + ({9})x + {-6} = 0}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>x^2+9 x-6=0</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>